# üì∑ Image Converter Tool
This tool helps you **convert images** from different formats (JPEG, PNG, GIF) into a **lighter format (WEBP by default)** to **save storage space and improve performance**. It also **preserves the original folder structure** and allows copying non-image files if needed.

## üîß How to Use
### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Place Your Images in the Input Folder
- Open the input folder inside this project.
- Put all your images inside.
- If you have subfolders, they will be kept the same in the output.
### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Run the Converter
- Open the Terminal.
- Navigate to the folder where the script is located using:
```bash
cd /path/to/the/folder
```
- Run the script:
```bash
node index.js
```
### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Get Your Converted Images
- Once finished, you will find the new images inside the output folder.
- The images will keep their original folders.
- The original images will not be deleted or modified.